My React app crashes when I load the user profile page. Here's the error:

TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'map')
    at UserProfile (src/components/UserProfile.jsx:23:34)
    at renderWithHooks (node_modules/react-dom/cjs/react-dom.development.js:16305:18)
    at mountIndeterminateComponent (node_modules/react-dom/cjs/react-dom.development.js:20069:13)

Here's the relevant code:

```jsx
function UserProfile({ userId }) {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch(`/api/users/${userId}`)
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => setUser(data));
  }, [userId]);

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{user.name}</h1>
      <ul>
        {user.posts.map(post => (
          <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
}
```

It works fine after I navigate to the page from elsewhere, but crashes on direct page load or refresh.
